<br>
Some others you might want to look at: <br>
<br>
• Goranga spiked club – it's a bit quicker and hits very hard. A very nice weapon, especially if you want to practice a bit.<br>
<br>
• Staff of Living Sand – I used this staff for a long time (yes, it is 2hb) and it makes a nice weapon. I usually hit in the 30s with it, with good hits (with buffs) into the 70s and 80s. Don't forget the weapon proc (225pt DoT).<br>
<br>
• Dark ember, which has been discussed before. Popular weapon, relatively affordable, nice stats.<br>
<br>
• Shimmering Mace. I still have one and I use it during raid situations when I need more wisdom and/or resists (It has magic and fire resists on it). It is part of the Cloak of Truth quest, obtained from Abrogast the Cleric in Katta Castellum. Chances are, if you are in a guild and someone is doing the quest, you can probably get one of these maces. Otherwise, even post a message in the Battlefield section if someone is questing for this cloak. Offer to help out healing with the final fight and I'm sure you stand a good chance of getting the mace. <br>
<br>
Right now, I still carry around my shimmering mace, my club of the ice ocean (which I would recommend, except it has a required level of 51), and my staff of living sand. There are  a lot of other good weapons I'd love to get  – the one I probably have the best chance of getting is the Witchdoctor's Cudgel, which drops in Nadox off High Priest Grumsalot. It's a very nice weapon (18/22 with a bunch of resists and stats, if I remember correctly) but it looks a little less imposing than many other weapons. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
